Take Control of your practice sessions, lower your handicap, and unlock your potential.

This app is going to change how you practice. It will reveal your weaknesses and help you focus on what really needs work. Perfect Practice will help you increase performance no matter who you are or your current skill level.


Football players practice on the field, basketball players practice on the court, swimmers practice in the pool, and baseball players practice on a baseball diamond. But, if you play golf you practice at the driving range. For us golfers, our practice tee does not resemble the golf course. Whether it is off of grass, a hitting mat, or inside in a simulator. Our practice area can be an obstacle for performance improvement.

How often do you change clubs at the range? 
How long do you take between shots, and does that time resemble the time between shots on the course?  What is the purpose of practicing golf? Ideally, it is to develop your skills as a golfer and to work on the pieces of the game that you are struggling with, so you can enjoy the game when you do play. Perfect practice for golf will help you overcome the shortcomings of the golf practice environment. 

How often do you get the same shot out on the course even if you are using the same club? 
Golf benefits tremendously from random practice.  Random practice is an effective way to sharpen your ability to execute on the course. Perfect Practice gives golfers the ability to get an honest random practice session in. In the random full swing mode, the app will issue distances that are within your ability based on the distances you entered in your profile when you set up your bag. Enter the outcome after each shot. The app will store the data so it can be viewed in your Profile under Clubs. Each practice session can also be viewed in a summary format on your mobile device, for quick reference of how well you performed at the end of your session. Random practice has a unique effect on the brain. It makes each shot more distinct from the next, which makes it more meaningful to the brain resulting in more elaborate memory representations. In other words, random practice on the range more easily translates to performance on the course. 



The app will get to know you over time. As it starts to identify your tendencies it will occasionally offer you Block and Serial practice sessions based on your performance to help you work on the things that you have struggled with.

What is your intention for the next shot? 
One of the best elements of Perfect Practice, is that it makes you slow down and think about what you are doing. Your practice will become more purposeful and you will find that you will need to hit fewer balls due to the fact that you are getting more out of each shot. It has been said that it takes 10,000 hours to gain mastery of a skill. The caveat in that idea is that, it is perfect practice that makes perfect. 

Less is more for many things, especially when quantity and quality are put in opposition to each other. Learning happens quicker when quality reps are made.


Slow Down
The app will slow you down and part of it is the data entry component. Go with it. It is a great distraction to prevent you from getting into a groove. Even if you are doing a customized block practice, enter in each shot. We recommend picking up the Iphone bag mount. It will keep your phone safe, and it will make data entry easier.
